* [[Orcs]] attempt to pierce the [[Pass of Aglon]], but they are defeated by [[Maedhros]] and [[Maglor]], who are aided by the sons of [[Finarfin]] and [[Edain]] of the [[House of Bëor]].<ref group=note>As written, this annal also contains "and [[Bëor]] was with them, the first of Men to draw sword in behalf of the Eldar", but was in a version where the House of Bëor entered Beleriand in the year {{FA|400|n}}, and the [[House of Haleth]] and [[House of Hador]] didn't enter until {{FA|420|n}}. It was not emended to account for the coming of Men much earlier, in {{FA|310|n}}, and Bëor's death in {{FA|355|n}}. In the revised genealogy, living members of the House of Bëor at this time included their chieftain, the elderly [[Boron]] (age 87), and future chieftains [[Boromir (Lord of Ladros)|Boromir]] (age 64), and [[Bregor]] (age 43).</ref><ref name="Annals">{{GA|125}}, p. 49</ref>

